race.comment: COOL ROCKER (5) wound up strongly last time out to finish one length adrift in third over 1550m at Manangatang on debut. Leading player again. KATIYA (10) put the writing on the wall last time when fourth at Manangatang over 1550m, beaten 1.3 lengths. Big chance to shed the maiden tag. IRLANDAIS (3) is a 23-start maiden who could only manage to finish ninth at his latest appearance over 2200m at Balaklava. Looks to be in the right race to play a big role. CUBAN DAWN (1) finished fourth two runs back then improved last start but found a couple better over 1600m at Moe, beaten 4 lengths. Well placed to feature in the finish.
